    "headline": "Bitcoin ‘Rage Quitting’ Sends It Slumping. Where Does It Go From Here?",
    "summary": "Things end with a whimper, not a bang, T.S. Eliot theorized in his 1925 poem “The Hollow Men,” a bleak assessment of life after the first world war.  Bitcoin  ongoing decline, and 40% slump from the heady heights of its late October record, might be undergoing a similar evolution, losing its luster to one of the biggest tech rallies on record and suffering some big name exits as it reaches the lowest levels since early April.  Mark Cuban, the billionaire former “Shark Tank” regular and erstwhile critic of President Donald Trump, dumped nearly all his bitcoin holdings late last month, saying the original digital currency has “lost the plot.”",
    "url": "https://www.barrons.com/articles/bitcoin-price-slump-cryptocurrencies-e7d0bbc6?siteid=yhoof2&yptr=yahoo",
